      <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-serif-display); font-size: 1.75rem; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Widow/Widower Tax Penalty</h3>
      <p style="line-height: 1.7; opacity: 0.9; font-size: 0.95rem;">One of the most overlooked tax traps in retirement is the widow/widower penalty. When a spouse dies, the surviving spouse must file as single the following year. The same income taxed at married-filing-jointly rates is now taxed at single rates with narrower brackets. A couple paying 15% could see the survivor jump to 22% or higher. Proactive Roth conversions and strategic income allocation can mitigate this before it happens.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

