<section class="ep-faq">
  <div class="ep-faq-inner">
    <div>
      <span class="ep-chapter-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="ep-faq-title">Tax Planning FAQ</h2>
      <p class="ep-faq-sub">Learn about strategic retirement tax planning to minimize your lifetime tax burden.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="ep-btn-ghost">Ask About Tax Planning</a>
    </div>
    <div>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What are the three tax buckets in retirement? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>The three tax buckets are: 1) Taxable accounts (pay taxes as you go), 2) Tax-deferred accounts like 401(k)s and traditional IRAs (pay taxes later), and 3) Tax-free accounts like Roth IRAs (never pay taxes again). Strategic withdrawal sequencing optimizes your tax burden.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How do Roth conversions reduce retirement taxes? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Roth conversions let you pay taxes now at potentially lower rates and enjoy tax-free growth and withdrawals forever. This is especially valuable if you expect higher tax rates in retirement or want to reduce RMDs.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What is tax-loss harvesting in retirement? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Tax-loss harvesting involves strategically selling investments at a loss to offset capital gains and reduce your tax burden. This can be particularly valuable in retirement when managing taxable account withdrawals.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How do RMDs affect my taxes and what can I do? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Required Minimum Distributions from traditional retirement accounts starting at age 73 can push you into higher tax brackets. Roth conversions before RMDs begin can reduce future tax impact.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What is IRMAA and how can I avoid it? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>IRMAA (Income-Related Monthly Adjustment Amount) is a Medicare surcharge for high earners. Strategic income management through withdrawal sequencing and Roth conversions can help you avoid these costly premiums.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Should I do charitable giving for tax benefits in retirement? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Qualified Charitable Distributions (QCDs) from your IRA directly to charity count toward your RMD but don't increase your taxable income. This can be a powerful tax strategy for charitable-minded retirees.</p></div>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

